untyped

forth in zig

goals:
  - remain true to core principles of forth
    - simplicity
    - directness
  - usable as a general purpose language on linux
  - embeddable in a larger program
    - should enable hot reloading of code
    - not afraid to define language features in zig as needed

features:
  - takes some things from ansi forth and gforth
  - floats
  - files
  - dictionaries
    - kindof like wordlists
    - useful for hot reloading

planned:
  - error reporting / stack traces
  - terminal drawing
  - usable as a shell
  - dynamic loading of object files to extend functionality

MIT
